<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-01-0087 </DOCNO><TEXT>The factors that have changed public attitudes towards the use of nuclearpower are reviewed. These are seen as the link between nuclear weaponsand nuclear power, radiation leaks and reactor accidents and the uneconomicnature of nuclear power. These aspects have resulted in the growth ofthe anti-nuclear movement. The strength of the nuclear lobby and thetrades unions are considered. A programme for action to end the use ofnuclear power in the UK is outlined. It is hoped that a major nuclearaccident will not provide the final argument. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>